id: pm-bnmlsc
title: "Sentry PM-CLI-2G: make merge-driver installation permission failures actionable"
description: "Sentry reports a handled high-severity production failure when pm merge install attempts to configure the repository-local merge driver in a workspace where .git/config cannot be locked. Harden the merge-install boundary so expected read-only or permission-constrained repositories return a deterministic, actionable pm error instead of surfacing a raw child-process failure, while preserving normal field-aware merge-driver installation."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags: []
created_at: "2026-07-21T21:51:22.939Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-21T22:11:32.531Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-21T22:11:15.084Z"
author: codex-root
parent: pm-92if
severity: high
environment: production CI and permission-constrained Git workspaces
repro_steps: Run pm merge install in a valid Git worktree where repository-local Git configuration cannot be written.
expected_result: "The command fails with a stable pm error code and remediation guidance, classifies the expected permission constraint appropriately in telemetry, and leaves Git configuration unchanged."
actual_result: "The underlying git config command fails with 'could not lock config file .git/config: Permission denied' and produces handled high-severity Sentry issue PM-CLI-2G."
affected_version: 2026.7.21
component: merge-install
customer_impact: Agents in read-only CI or sandboxed worktrees receive a raw infrastructure error and observability records an expected environmental constraint as a high-severity product failure.
